I"<p>Given that <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memory-induces-coherence">people actively reshape ideas for worldview coherence</a>, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/parallel-distributed-processing-is-resilient-and-efficient">centralized</a> hubs should be avoided in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/computer-networking-idealizes-social-structures">social networks</a> in order to avoid groupthink, a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/global-minimum-is-not-the-target-in-machine-learning">local optimum</a> in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memeplexes-resemble-grativational-attractors">memetic evolution</a>. <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/knowledge-graph-connectivity-quantifies-knowledge-work">Connectivity</a> should be increased, resulting in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/diversity-in-problem-solving-sidesteps-ideological-debt">sidestepping ideological debt</a>. For an individual, this means <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-makes-consumption-creation-ratio-salient">consuming</a> content from diverse sources. However, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/information-hygiene-is-like-spacecraft-sanitization">information hygiene issues</a> might manifest.</p>
